Apple's HomeKit offfers a unique opportunity for devices to be controlled by Siri or iOS clients.  Our value proposition is around ease of internetworking silos, enabling hyper-local content, context, and services.  We utlize Content Centric Networking and Named-Function Network as a mechanism to ensure secure communication and ease integration time to market that plagues the first generation of HomeKit products.  IoTone has signed its first licensee and is expecting to release in January 2016. Description: Peeka is a social saving website that uses collective demand to reduce prices and offer savings on gift cards.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Peeka.com is a social saving website that uses collective demand to reduce prices and offer savings on thousands of gift cards.  On peeka.com, the prices of gift cards are hidden and start at their retail value. Customers must purchase peeks, which cost $.20, and ‘peek’ at the item in order to reveal its price.  $.10 of the ‘peek’ is used towards reducing the price and the customer is then given 15 seconds to decide whether or not to purchase the gift card.   If a customer chooses to purchase the gift card, they may check out and will receive it via email. If not, the gift card is put back on Peeka.com at the newly discounted price and the savings are passed on to future customers.  Peeka uses the collective interest and “peeks” to generate savings which are passed on to the consumer.
Industry Groups: Commerce and Shopping, Consumer Electronics, Financial Services, Hardware

Full Description: DateUp’s mission is to create the best dating experience for tall women, but people of all heights are welcome.  DateUp helps tall people find love by removing the guesswork in online dating. DateUp matches tall people with other tall people nearby, or with shorter people that are interested in tall matches. Men 6'0"+ and women 5'8"+ join as "Members," and can match with other Members or with "Guests." Guests are shorter people interested in "dating-up." The idea of DateUp was sparked by the clear difficulty that tall women face when dating. In particular, it can be difficult for tall women to find other tall men or shorter men that are comfortable with dating-up.  DateUp offers a safe place for tall people to find height-compatible matches with other tall people nearby, or with shorter people that want to date-up. DateUp is intentionally designed to create a balance between an exclusive and inclusive experience.
